  "text": "Complex and realistic models with a high level of detail can be created by blending many implicit primitives as demonstrated in [CITATION_1] . In this approach the primitives not only define the density distribution but also the shape of the cloud. While this approach is effective for modeling a few clouds, it does not scale well and cannot be used to model large cloudscapes.",
